text: Godwin of Wessex (died 15 April 1053) was an Anglo-Saxon earl, the head of a noble and rich family in Wessex. He was the father of King Harold II () and of Edith of Wessex. Edith married King Edward the Confessor in 1045 (). Category:Earls and countesses Category:Anglo-Saxons
title: Godwin, Earl of Wessex
